{"sections":{"main":{"type":"main-page","disabled":true,"settings":{}},"f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"Caring for your Leather"}},"template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"enlarge_text":false,"text":"<p>Leather is a natural product and will develop a patina and unique character over time and with wear. Good leather, like ours at NOVO, ages well to make it one of the most long-lasting materials, really coming into its own after some heavy use as long as you look after it. <\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-0","template--15944288010406__f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0-1667561139e0a1884c-1"],"settings":{"align_text":"center","narrow_column":true,"divider":false}},"a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c":{"type":"slideshow","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c-1667561124a81e7b1c-0":{"type":"image","settings":{"top_subheading":"","title":"","title_size":40,"subheading":"","link":"","link_text":"","link_2":"","link_text_2":"","color_accent":"rgba(0,0,0,0)","text_align":"vertical-center horizontal-center","image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/leather_banner.webp","parallax_direction":"top","overlay_opacity":0,"focal_point":"center center"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c-1667561124a81e7b1c-0"],"settings":{"section_height":"550px","mobile_height":"auto","parallax":false,"style":"bars","autoplay":true,"autoplay_speed":5}},"c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-0":{"type":"heading","settings":{"title":"Our Guide To Caring For Leather"}},"template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"enlarge_text":false,"text":"<p>01.<\/p><p>Leather can be spot cleaned with a slightly damp cloth.<\/p><p>02.<\/p><p>Keep leather supple and conditioned with a specialist leather balm. Apply a small amount with a cloth and buff gently. <\/p><p>03.<\/p><p>Hang leather garments to ventilate between wears, avoiding direct sunlight. <\/p><p>04.<\/p><p>When travelling and storing, roll leather garments to avoid fold creases. <\/p><p>05.<\/p><p>Softer leathers can scratch! Be careful with sharp items like keys and also take particular care when storing in your wardrobe and indents can happen when items are compressed against something else.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-0","template--15944288010406__c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd-1667561139e0a1884c-1"],"settings":{"align_text":"center","narrow_column":true,"divider":false}},"6cdb4a11-f84e-44bb-a5f3-336c3128122c":{"type":"featured-collection","settings":{"title":"Shop Leather","home_featured_products":"leather","per_row":3,"rows":1,"mobile_scrollable":true,"view_all":false,"divider":true}},"29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"template--15944288010406__29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433-16675625010eb8cfaa-1":{"type":"text","settings":{"enlarge_text":false,"text":"<p><a href=\"\/pages\/garment-care\" title=\"Garment Care\"><strong>Back to Garment Care Guides<\/strong><\/a><\/p>"}}},"block_order":["template--15944288010406__29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433-16675625010eb8cfaa-1"],"settings":{"align_text":"center","narrow_column":true,"divider":false}}},"order":["main","f86dd9ed-708b-4ec8-a64e-3fc60efe68c0","a66daebe-90aa-4ca8-abe2-c7fbec53a30c","c9331514-3497-46b1-b621-60df9ec5b2bd","6cdb4a11-f84e-44bb-a5f3-336c3128122c","29bb3435-63c6-484f-bf2f-627c6cacb433"]}